title: Kyrgyzstan election: President Jeenbekov resigns after protests
snippet: Kyrgyz President Sooronbay Jeenbekov has resigned after days of protests following a disputed election that plunged the country into turmoil.

title: Kyrgyz President Jeenbekov Offers Resignation – The Diplomat
snippet: Jeenbekov continued that he did “not want to be known in the history of Kyrgyzstan as a president who spilled blood and shot at his own citizens,” he said. “Therefore, I decided to resign.”

title: Kyrgyz President Jeenbekov announces resignation - CGTN
snippet: Kyrgyz President Sooronbai Jeenbekov resigned on Thursday, saying he wanted to prevent clashes between security forces and protesters who have demanded his removal from office, the country's Kabar News Agency reported.

title: Kyrgyzstan: President Sooronbay Jeenbekov steps down
snippet: Kyrgyzstan’s president Sooronbay Jeenbekov announced his resignation in a desire to avoid further violence. Sadyr Japarov is the interim president.

title: Sooronbay Jeenbekov: Kyrgyzstan president announces resignation | News | Al Jazeera
snippet: Kyrgyzstan’s President Sooronbay Jeenbekov resigned on Thursday, saying he wanted to bring an end to a crisis which was sparked by disputed parliamentary elections earlier this month.
